snippet.textDisplay: Video and music taking me back to when I was younger, and a few bouts as an adult. No meds for me consistently, but I had behavior issues, and couldn't focus; I'm pretty sure "it's" the reason I was treated like a moron through school, and tested with IQ scores well above average. The schools aren't set up to handle people who are not on the normal pace and who can't control their focus better. Still I don't condone giving speed to my kid, who is going through something similar.
